rComments: I gained a lot of insight from this course. I really enjoyed the bit on self-compassion as that I never knew of this concept before. I appreciated that she took the time outside of class to have interesting conversations. The workload was comparable to other online classes. She's a straight shooter and is overt about her expectations unlike others.

2 take home midterms and 2 assignments. Pretty standard hybrid course. The assignments were quite easy but the exams were a bit long. If you're well prepared and attend class, you'll get a good grade. She's a great lecturer and chooses modern topics. Very kind through email and in-person. She really wants everyone to succeed & is very flexible.

Course content was stimulating and extremely inclusive. I really appreciated this. Great lecturer and I would definitely take a course with her again! She gave lots of feedback, answered emails promptly, and is very compassionate and understanding if you're struggling. Exams were a bit tough and made you apply your knowledge but I learned so much!

I had a terrible experience in this class. I had many tutors and studied more for this class than any of my higher level courses. She does not respond to emails often and I received very little feedback on the papers that she claimed were Fs. Not pleased with the money Ive spent on this course.

This class was a mandatory class I had to take. Two assignments and two take-home exams. The take-home exams would take up to a week to complete and it was very difficult to receive a good mark. The class average was very low. She had great lectures but her assignments take-home exams structure was not very well done.
